cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.SI 

This paper deals with the security and privacy of messaging, specifically email encryption. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses decentralized key distribution, which falls under cs.CY (Computers and Society). The implementation of ClaimChain involves distributed systems, which could be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the implementation of ClaimChain in email clients, which falls under cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper discusses privacy-preserving authentication, which could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
